	</script><BR><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td><font class="h1font">Type II: Intermediate Decks</font></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
<tr height="10"><td width="98%" bgcolor="#669933" height="10"><img src="/magic/gfx/trans.gif" width="6" height="2" vspace="0" hspace="0" border="0"></td><td valign="bottom" align="right"><img src="/magic/gfx/hrz/tg.gif" width="103" height="10" border="0" vspace="0" hspace="0"></td>
</tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td valign="top" align="right">
<img src="/magic/gfx/hrz/bg.gif" width="92" height="24" border="0" vspace="0" hspace="0"></td>
</tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><font class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font class="h1font">Traumatizing Echoes</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><table width='80' border='0' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='0'><tr><td background='/lotr/gfx/5star.gif'><img src='/lotr/gfx/trans.gif' width='1' height='25'></td></tr></table><font size=1>(4)</font> | <A HREF="/magic/decks/decks.php?reviews=25881">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/magic/main/mpage.php?member=12729">Justin "Sevarian" Mathers</A></FONT> <font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/magic/main/mpage.php?member=12729&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Make your opponent discard half of his deck with Traumatize. Then cast Haunting echoes and leave him with only lands to fight you with.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> October 11, 2002</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Blue<br>
2-4 Traumatize (put in 4 if you can&#39;t get 4 diabolic tutors)<br>
4 Careful Study<br>
4 Counterspells<br>
<br>
Black<br>
2-4 Haunting Echoes (put in 4 if you can&#39;t get 4 diabolic tutors)<br>
4 Diabolic Tutors<br>
<br>
Creatures<br>
**I know these are supposed to be put in with the cards of there color but, it really doesnt matter what creatures you decide to put in the deck, because the main idea is to leave him defenseless, I prefer small/low casting creatures That i can get out to chump block incase they rush me early**<br>
<br>
Land<br>
12 Swamp<br>
13 Islands<br>
<br>
Sideboard<br>
(Only Sideboard for blue)<br>
2 Islands<br>
4 Gainsays (To protect from blue counterspells)   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Make sure you have your Traumatizes first round, even though you cant cast them for a while, you dont want to have to search for it later. You should be able to get that in no more than two mulligans. If not, never fear you have diabolic tutors to get them for you. Then whenever you get the chance next get your Haunting echoes in your hand ready to cast also. Use any creatures you have to block creature attacks. As far as counterspells, if facing a red opponent, counter the big burn, if facing a blue opponent you might want to save till you cast your Tramatize and Haunting echoes to make sure they can&#39;t counter that. Then when you have the mana cast Traumatize, your opponent will take half of his/her deck rounded down and put it in their graveyard. Then on your next turn cast Haunting Echoes; Not only does your opponent remove all of his/her graveyard from the game, but they also go through their deck and remove all cards that are the same as those removed from the graveyard(Other than basic lands). So basically other than what they have left is the cards in their hand and land...They have to have soem serious luck to beat you after that :^) </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/magic/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/magic/decks/decks.php?reviews=25881"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=25881" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/magic/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font><BR></td></tr></table> <!-- #EndEditable --></td>
          <td width="1" valign="top" ><img src="/magic/gfx/trans.gif" width="9" height="2" vspace="0" hspace="0" border="0"></td>
        </tr>
